Because Dart Isolates have separate memory spaces, the background Database Isolate (which performs the batch import) has its own memory heap. 
Since all batch writes (`dbUpdateAll` / `updateAllRaw`) are offloaded to this background Isolate, it will populate and use its own `_businessKeyCache` inside its thread memory.

